dcterms:creator: M. Redmond
A. Baveja
dcterms:description: A dataset concerned with predicting per capita violent crime rate in different communities in the United States from a set of relevant features, such as median family income or the percentage of people under the poverty line. Race is considered the sensitive variable.
dcterms:title: Communities and Crime

dcterms:creator: D. Dheeru
E. Karra Taniskidou
dcterms:description: The Adult dataset contains information about individuals, including features such as age, education, and occupation, used to predict whether a person's income exceeds $50K per year. The dataset includes sensitive variables like gender and race.
dcterms:title: Adult Income
